Title: On the Road
Author: Jack Kerouac
My Review:
Before to read the book I have seen a few reviews.
Around the hundredth page, I thought: looks like it can be read just like a book.
Around the two hundredth page: why when I lived like this, there were no publishers who paid money for describing like that.
Thirty pages to the end: O, about thirty pages left.
Then on the moment that they wrote each other letters of eight thousand words: I become to respected that old-fashioned time.
And when I finished. I think it's good reading and this book has made my reading experience more complete.
